
                                            This weekend officers were once again deployed to roadblocks across the province, checking documentation, roadworthiness and driver sobriety.
                                         CAPE TOWN - Since Friday evening, the Western Cape Traffic Department says it issued close to half a million rand in fines. This weekend officers were once again deployed to roadblocks across the province, checking documentation, roadworthiness and driver sobriety. Western Cape traffic chief Kenny Africa said: “At the end of the day we arrested 15 drunken drivers and the highest reading recorded was a reading 1,47 milligrams per 1000 millilitres and that was in the Southern Cape in George.  This driver was six times over the legal limit.” Africa says his department also recorded 146 speeding incidents. “The total amount of fines that we issued was R459 200.”